texts.text: >In Tokyo's Akihabara district,
>crowds of people are enjoying their time off.
Okay, comrade. Let's review today's itinerary.
Right! First, we'll shop for the latest idol goods!
Then, we'll head over to the concert! I am so hyped!
Ditto! Our support will make or break this show!
Let's tear some vocal chords!
Yes, I concur!

Plus, we couldn't ask for more perfect weather.
...Huh?
What do you think that is, comrade?
>The man points to the air rippling in front of them.
I'm not sure. A heat haze, maybe?
At this temperature? No way.
Then what could it be...?
Grrr....
Huh? That sounded like a growl.
>All at once, the warped space expands.
>Then...!
*Roar*
*Scream*
What IS that thing?! Hey, stay back! I mean it!!
Someone! Anyone! Help!
The fuck?! Where'd you come from?!
Yo, speak up! My bro just asked you a question!
How very rude of me. As an apology...
I shall grant you both death.
*Scream*
*Shriek*
Wh-What is this freak?!
*Roar*

Kyaaaah!
S-Someone, save me!
I'll hold it back, so escape while you can!
Y-Yes! Thank you!
...This demon suddenly appeared from a warp hole.
Wait, it's not the only one...

Eeeeeeek!
Wh-What is that thing?!
Please!! Someone save ussss!
What in the world is going...
*Roar*
...! Devil Download!
...The time has come.
We have patiently awaited the day of our revenge.
With this newfound power, the Divine shall stand no chance.
My oppressed servants. Release your long-withheld fury upon the land.
Divine. Fear me and remember this name:
I am Rahab, Sower of Chaos.
>Several hours later.
Sorry to call on your day off, but we got a situation, y'all.
You might've seen 'em already, but demons are runnin' around town.
And not just one or two. We're talkin' an assload of 'em.
I requested backup, but there's a lot of ground to cover.
Even if every branch works together, things still look dicey.
However, civilian lives are in our hands.
So, let's get out there and kick some demon ass!
Yes. We shall defend the people of this city.
Go Team!
I'm scared.
That's the spirit, Newbie. I'm countin' on ya.
Do not let fear control you. We are can protect ourselves, after all.
Let's do our best to save those who can not.
Cool pep-talk, but we first need to figure out the cause of this.
You said it. Too bad we've got nothin' to go on.
I hate to say it, but for now all we can do is damage control.
No, that shall not be necessary.
...! Who're you?!
It's been a while, those bound to the Heralds.
A Divine?! Wait...
You look kinda familiar...
Yeah, we've definitely met before.
It was back when those demons were huntin' down theologians.
Humans, the demons here were intentionally set loose.
The culprit is Rahab, who exists in an alternate dimension.
Rahab?
That's the demon behind all this?
Correct.
You must swiftly defeat him above all else.
Do not save anyone. Your only priority is to vanquish Rahab.
...You better check that attitude.
...Defeating him is certainly vital.
However, we cannot allow anymore people to suffer.
This is not a request. It is an order from the Heralds.
Surely you haven't forgotten.
You are all soldiers under contract in the Lord's Army.
Hold up, I didn't sign nothin'.
Vince and I are our own people. You can't order us around.
Yeah, none of us agreed to any contract!
This shitty con angel is just blowin' smoke.
...Yo, we've got no plans to join God's Army, ya hear?
But we'll help take down the Big Bad for humanity's sake.
So, we want intel. Tell us what you know.
How asinine. You cannot break our contract for any reason.
You shall find Rahab andâ€”
*Howl*
>A demon appears out of nowhere and bites the Divine's neck.
Whoa! Where'd Fido come from?!
Devil Download!
We beat the demon, but...
We failed to save that Divine.
And our only lead is the name of their head honcho.
Still, this is no time for a pity party. News just arrived.
Demons have been spotted all across the city.
Other Dx2 patrol units are locked in a full-scale battle.
Tch. Things are already gettin' out of hand.
No use cryin' now. Let's investigate while we defend the city.
Time to roll out! Playtime's over for these demons!
